cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a spreading process on a network and its underlying spatial structure. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the construction of a "contagion map" for a spreading process. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible category as the paper uses numerical methods to study the spreading dynamics on the network. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the topology and geometry of the point cloud generated by the contagion map. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the propagation of a contagion on a network.
